{
  "stem": "18281.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 92.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Half of those 200,000 Jews were assimilated Jews like ourselves that considered themselves Austrian first.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then you had the poor-- as I mentioned to you-- the, the, the refugees that reached German-speaking countries.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, if you recall your history of the First World War, Hindenburg, who was even then an aging leader of-- general of the German army won a tremendous battle, the Battle of Tannenberg, which was fought very close to the Russian-Polish border.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Those battles were raging back and forth.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't have to tell you that when troops occupy a shtetl in Poland, the first thing that the, the whatever soldiers just conquered this village, the first thing they do is rape and steal and rob the local populations.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So those poor people fled the, the battles of the First World War and reached German-speaking countries like Austria or Germany.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Second, their emotion was that they-- when they forced Jews into the Polish army, those guys didn't really survive very long.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Besides having the enemy to fight, they also had their Polish comrades to fight.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If they saw a Jew, they more or less killed him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So those people, in order to escape the draft, fled Poland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you asked first about the Viennese.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Viennese did not like Jews, period. 1,000 years of church rantings against the Christ killers had really educated the Austrian masses.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The only difference between those Polish Jews in Vienna and ourselves was that we were not easily recognizable.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We really could pass for Austrians.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were not discriminated against, because people didn't know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "If you meet me or my dad on the street, you didn't know that we were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Well, those people stuck out like a sore thumb.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
